.git

# Secrets: docker-compose.yml's `web` service reads .env.docker via `env_file` at
# container *start* from the host, so nothing here is needed at runtime — but
# without these, `docker build`'s COPY would still bake real secrets (service-role
# key, admin passwords, supabase/.env.local's TMDB token) into an image layer,
# outliving any later key rotation. Unlike .gitignore, .dockerignore does NOT treat
# a bare pattern as matching at every depth -- `*.local` alone only matches at the
# build context root, silently missing supabase/.env.local. Every pattern here
# must be `**/`-prefixed to actually be recursive (verified by building the image
# and inspecting its filesystem, not just reading the pattern text).
**/*.local
**/.env
**/.env.docker
